		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>Rod - Very Rare (Requires Attunement)</em></p><p><strong>Buff</strong></p><ul><li><p>When you attune to the rod, you learn how many levels of energy it has absorbed overall and how many levels remain stored.</p></li><li><p>If you're a spellcaster, you can convert stored energy into spell slots you have prepared or know, creating slots up to level 5 and no higher than your normal slot maximum (for example, spend 3 levels to cast a level 3 spell).</p></li><li><p>A newly discovered rod typically holds [[/r 1d10]] levels of energy. A rod that can neither absorb further energy nor has energy remaining becomes nonmagical.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Reaction</strong></p><ul><li><p>When a spell targets only you and creates no area of effect, you can absorb it. The spell is canceled and its energy--not the spell itself--is stored in the rod at the spell's level. The rod can store up to 50 levels of energy over its lifetime; spells it cannot store are unaffected.</p></li></ul><section class=\"secret\" id=\"foundry-secret-1\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>This item has a max of 50 uses for tracking the total <strong>energy absorbed</strong>. You can roll 1d10 and update the expended uses and the <strong>Available</strong> energy in the description above as desired.</p><p>The <strong>Absorb Spell</strong> activity allows you to select the spell level you're absorbing and expends a number of uses. You should then manually update the <strong>Available</strong> amount of energy in the description above.</p><p>The <strong>Restore Slot</strong> activity allows you to restore a spell slot. You should then manually update the <strong>Available</strong> amount of energy in the description above.</p></section>",
